laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT Abdomen/Pelvis with and without contrast
laboratory_examinations.findings: Lower chest: unchanged right lung base pulmonary cyst; no pleural or pericardial effusion. Abdomen: liver normal, pancreas normal, spleen normal, kidneys normal with resolved hydroureteronephrosis, wall thickening from rectosigmoid to sigmoid colon more prominent than prior study; mild sigmoid diverticulosis noted.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Hydroureteronephrosis on the left has resolved. Wall thickening and tethering from the rectosigmoid to sigmoid colon slightly more prominent compared to the prior study.
